The Excellence in Education Awards Ceremony, originally scheduled for April 16th, was postponed due to the COVID-19 pandemic. While it was disappointing that this celebration was postponed, the new virtual format allows for more participants to join the recognition of our 54 Teacher of the Year honorees on Tuesday, September 15, 2020.

Please join Anne Arundel County Public Schools, the 21st Century Education Foundation, and our Headline Sponsors, BGE & Comcast, as we honor our amazing Anne Arundel County teachers starting at 6 pm on AACPS-TV and streaming at

This family-friendly program will air on AACPS TV throughout the month of September. https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PL63heeIfctOs2FYO3xjXScHUbfmJHnwmk

Anne Arundel County Police Department
September 3 at 5:26 PM ·

UPDATE: Nasir has been located and is safe. Thank you!

#Missing

Please help us locate Nasir Malik Phoenix who is reported missing from Millersville. He is 17 years old, 5’8” tall, and 190 lbs. If you have any information regarding Nasir or his whereabouts, please contact 911 or the Anne Arundel County Police Department Missing Persons Squad at 410.222.8763. Individuals wishing to remain anonymous may call the Tip Line at 410.222.4700.

post_text: Superintendent George Arlotto will discuss the reopening of schools with members of the county delegation to the General Assembly during a virtual meeting of the delegation at 9 a.m. on Monday, August 24. The public can view the meeting on AACPS-TV, which can be found on Channel 96 on Comcast and Broadstripe, and Channel 36 on Verizon. High definition broadcasts can be seen on Channel 996 on Comcast, Channel 496 on Broadstripe, and Channel 1961 on Verizon. The meeting will also be broadcast on AACPS’ YouTube channel at www.aacps.org/youtube.

post_text:
To fully engage students in virtual learning this fall, AACPS will issue Chromebooks to every student. To help support families with the most technological needs first, please take a few minutes to complete this survey as soon as possible.

You will need your child's student ID number to complete the survey, which can be found on your child's report card or by contacting your child's school Monday-Thursday between 8 a.m and 2 p.m.

Please note that students enrolled at contract and charter schools will receive separate communications on their schools' plans for devices. Those students should not complete this survey.

www.aacps.org/chromebooksurvey www.aacps.org/chromebooksurveySpanish

To fully engage students in virtual learning this fall, AACPS will issue Chromebooks to every student. To help support families with the most technological needs first, please take a few minutes to complete this survey as soon as possible.

You will need your child's student ID number to complete the survey, which can be found on your child's report card or by contacting your child's school Monday-Thursday between 8 a.m and 2 p.m.

Please note that students enrolled at contract and charter schools will receive separate communications on their schools' plans for devices. Those students should not complete this survey.

www.aacps.org/chromebooksurvey www.aacps.org/chromebooksurveySpanish

In addition, AACPS hopes to administer the SAT to seniors on Wednesday, October 14, 2020.

post_text: Our entire Anne Arundel County Public Schools family joins in mourning the loss of Mo Gaba, who passed away today after a long and courageous battle with cancer. Mo, a Baltimore Orioles Hall of Famer and sports fan extraordinaire, was a bright light to everyone he encountered. His joy and endless optimism throughout all of his trials were a source of strength for us all. #MoStrong was not just who he was, but who he inspired us all to become. Our thoughts and prayers go out to the entire Gaba family, especially Mo’s mom, Sonsy. We will remain #MoStrong for them.

post_text: It’s not every day that two award-winning musicians drop in on your high school graduation, but not every high school counts the Brothers Osborne among their alumni. Proud Southern High School grads John and T.J. Osborne asked if they could stop by with a few words of advice and well wishes for the Class of 2020. We thought it was an #AACPSAwesome idea. Thanks, guys!

post_text: County Executive Steuart Pittman may provide more clarity on Anne Arundel County's next steps with regard to reopening today.
shared_text:
County Executive Steuart Pittman
May 27 at 10:34 PM ·

Today, Governor Larry Hogan announced additional Stage 1 reopening actions. Our Anne Arundel public health metrics are showing improvement, and I am consulting with Anne Arundel County Department of Health to discuss how we can implement additional policies in the coming days. https://aahealth.org/reopening-dashboard-status-report/

We must be thoughtful with our approach, and put responsible policies in place that protect residents and businesses alike as we continue to move toward reopening. I will be meeting tomorrow with my recovery work group and expect to announce our path forward tomorrow afternoon.

We must be thoughtful with our approach, and put responsible policies in place that protect residents and businesses alike as we continue to move toward reopening. I will be meeting tomorrow with my recovery work group and expect to announce our path forward tomorrow afternoon.
